More than 700 Asiatic black bears have died at illegal bile farms in Vietnam in the past year . 
  Owners are killing them to 'extract the last ounce of blood' and sell body parts to China for use in traditional medicine . 
  Up to four bears killed in one day on some farms . 
  In Halong Bay 30 out of 49 captive bears died in the last three months . 
  British charity Animals Asia is fighting to save them . 
 